radio_info.short: KBQI (107.9 FM, "Big I 107.9") is a radio station in Albuquerque, New Mexico, owned by Clear Channel. It has a contemporary country music format.
radio_info.rest: It takes its name from the I-40 and I-25 interchange near downtown Albuquerque that is locally known as "the Big I". At the time of the station's launch in July 2000, the "Big I" was at the start of a major reconstruction project which had finished in May 2002. In February 2006 the station began broadcasting in HD Radio with an additional HD-2 subchannel that plays country variety.

radio_info.short: At Static Radio, they drown out the noise—all the junk the world pushes out at us as acceptable content. The gospel they relay is unchanging;
radio_info.rest: so they shoot straight to the character of the gospel. It is unchanging, unwavering, and doesn't need to "present itself" as relevant because the fact is: it is. It is so real that sometimes it hurts, convicts, and even offends. The word static means (among other things) "showing little or no change; constant." In technology, static means "unaffected by the passage of time, or the presence or absence of power."

radio_info.short: Welcome to Real Oldies 1600, Albuquerque’s Fabulous 50s and Super 60s station! We still believe in rock and roll, that music can change your mortal
radio_info.rest:
soul. And that real oldies and friendly people can be just the ticket to put you in a great mood.

We have the largest oldies library in town and program what we play based totally on your input. You can write to us via feedback@realoldies1600 or call us anytime at 505 931-1600.

We’re dedicated to serving the Albuquerque community but are proud of the thousands of listeners from around the world who hear us on-line.

So come join the fun! Meet the Real Oldies Air Force. Call us with a song request. And watch this space for information about Real Oldies remote broadcast where you can visit with us in person.

Listen Online & Feel Fine!

Hell0 & thanks to the hundreds of new listeners we’re picking up each week On-Line! We stream Real Oldies to your home, your office and to the world and listening to your favorite Real DJs is as easy as clicking the Listen Live Link. Yup, your computer can be a radio and you can take Real Oldies wherever you go! Speaking of On-Line, Real Oldies 1600 now has a Facebook Page and a presence at twitter.com/realoldies1600. Join the growing number of people who follow us, up to the minute on your favorite social network!

Shoot me an Email with your feedback, suggestions and comments, Or Call our 24 Hour Comment Line: (505) 931-1600. After all, Real Oldies 1600 is all about -you-!

The soundtrack of your life is alive and well on Real Oldies 1600!

Craig Collins
“Double C”
Operations Manager

radios.title: Native Voice One

radio_info.short: Native Voice One (NV1) educates, advocates, and celebrates Native American life and culture by providing a program service from a Native point of view. This
radio_info.rest:
service is for everyone interested in Native American news, culture, music, events, and life.

NV1 enables Native people, especially those who do not have access to the many reservation and village-based Native owned and operated stations, to stay connected. Many Native stations and independent radio producers contribute Native-oriented programs to NV1 for inclusion in the NV1 program service.

------
Shows: Earthsongs, AlterNative Voices, National Native News, American Indian Living, Native America Calling, UnderCurrents, Reach the Rez Radio podcast, The Native Voice, Voices from the Circle, Wisdom of the Elders

Our DJs have weekly shows with free-form formats consisting of indie rock and pop, emo and post punk, punk, hip hop, alternative, metal, electronica, jazz, world, blues, folk, talk, and more. Student radio at Texas A&M has been around for almost 35 years, and KANM is proud to continue this tradition.

radios.title: Albuquerque Area Air Route Traffic Control Center (ARTCC)

radio_info.short: Albuquerque Air Route Traffic Control Center (ZAB) is located Albuquerque, New Mexico, United States. The Albuquerque ARTCC is one out of 22 Air Route Traffic
radio_info.rest: Control Centers in the United States. The primary responsibility is the separation of overflights, and the expedited sequencing of arrivals and departures along STARs (Standard Terminal Arrival Routes) and SIDs (Standard Instrument Departures) for the airspace over most of Arizona and New Mexico, as well as parts of California, Colorado, Oklahoma, and Texas.

radio_info.short: A lot of radio stations suffer from fragmented formats unable to maintain quarter-hour appeal. With the consistency of Millennium Media stations, you know exactly the
radio_info.rest:
demographics you are targeting everyday! When it comes to providing results for the greater Gallup and Grants area, North Western New Mexico, South Western Colorado, North Eastern Arizona, and South Eastern Utah, one combination stands above the rest..


The trade area for Gallup is considered to be 150,000 people. The three counties of McKinley, Cibola, and San Juan, that are the heart of the market, have some 190,000 population.

Millennium Media stations appeal to the diverse demographics of the area which contains 50% Native Americans, 16% Hispanics and 34% White/Others. The transportation system includes Interstate 40 East West and U.S. 491 North-South.

The economy centers on retail trade, ranching, Native American arts and crafts, mineral extraction, coal-burning electrical power generating stations, and tourism.

Millennium Media has owned and operated radio stations in Gallup for thirty-two years, and has been a leader in the civic, cultural, and non-profit organizations of the area. Its employees have served as chairmen of the Chamber of Commerce, Rotary, and, the New Mexico Broadcasters Association.

They have been appointed by various Mayors to serve on important City commissions, and on the Board of Northwest New Mexico Council of Governments.

Many local non-profits attribute their inception and on-going success to monetary contributions, publicity and participation of Millennium Media, Inc. staff members. They have been honored on numerous occasions for these contributions.

radios.title: KRSN AM 1490 FM 107.1 - KRSN

radio_info.short: KRSN AM 1490 broadcasts from the Pajarito Plateau reaching Los Alamos, Espanola, Pojoaque , Santa Fe, and the areas in between. That means over 250,000
radio_info.rest:
people can hear us.  We entertain and inform our listening public through locally produced and syndicated shows captivating local interests .  We broadcast national and local news.  Local issues are included through features and interviews.

                KRSN is dedicated to being involved  in and an integral part of the communities we serve.  We participate in community activities and events as participants, sponsors, organizers, promoters or broadcasters. We are a proud Diamond level  donor for the United Way of Northern New Mexico.  We are a Platinum donor for the Los Alamos Summer Concert Series. KRSN is the primary sponsor of the Empty Bowls Event for Self Help Inc.

 We act as the primary sponsor for the Empty Bowls Event held in March for the benefit of Self Help Inc.  2009 was the 40th year Self Help
assisted members of our community.  It was the 16th annual Empty Bowls Project.  The event was in danger of being discontinued due to lack of sponsors until KRSN AM 1490 proudly stepped in and provided the volunteers, publicity, and storage space needed to produce the most successful bowl sale in event history.  Empty Bowls 2010 was held again on the second Saturday in March.  It was a little more successful than 2009 and raised over $9,000 for Self Help

------
